Q1)what is constructor ?what are the diffrent constructor in java prog?
Ans-A constructor is a special type of method which is used to invokes at the time of creation of object.
    Syntax-<class_name>(){} 
                  Meenu()
                     {
          		            // sop
	                   }
Types of constructor
1)Default Constructor:default constructor provide default value and those value depends on its type..
2)Parameterized Constructor: A constructor have parameter value.

